MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: packages/shared-types/src/index\.ts
MATCH_CONTENT: PromptCartridgeInput
ADVISORY: |
  When extending `PromptCartridgeInput` with a new field (e.g., adding `options?: string[]`
  or `promptId?: string` for a prompt-type-specific feature), the field does NOT
  automatically flow from the START_ACTIVITY payload to the cartridge machine's input.

  The spawner at `apps/game-server/src/machines/actions/l3-activity.ts:spawnPromptCartridge`
  builds the `input` object by explicitly picking fields off `event.payload` — any new
  field you add to `PromptCartridgeInput` must ALSO be added there, or it silently
  arrives as `undefined` and the machine falls back to its default.

  Flow:  START_ACTIVITY payload → spawnPromptCartridge input-builder → machine context

  Real session cost (2026-04-18): HOT_TAKE pool machine correctly spawned with the
  pool-picked question's options in `START_ACTIVITY.payload.options`, but the spawner
  only forwarded `optionA`/`optionB` (WYR's flat pair). Machine got `input.options ===
  undefined` and fell back to `['AGREE','DISAGREE']`. Three-option UI never rendered.
  Caught only by live browser verification, after spec + plan + full test suite all
  passed. Unit tests called the machine directly — they never exercised the spawner.

  Also update the machine context builder at `apps/game-server/src/machines/cartridges/prompts/<type>-machine.ts`
  to read `input.<new-field>`.
